# SPDX-License-Identifier: AGPL-3.0-or-later
#
# Trivy vulnerability ignore list.
#
# Each line is a CVE ID (or a Trivy vuln ID) that the scanner should
# skip. Comments are allowed and encouraged — silence without context
# is technical debt waiting to happen. Every entry must have:
#
#   - The CVE / GHSA ID being ignored
#   - Why we cannot fix it today (typically: pinned upstream is stale)
#   - When this was last reviewed and the next expected review date
#
# This file is consumed by `.github/workflows/security.yml` via the
# `ignorefile:` input on the `trivy-action`. Removing an entry here
# means the next PR will fail the gate until the vuln is fixed.
#
# Reviewed: 2026-07-13
# Next review: 2026-08-13 (one month) or on Caddy upstream action

# Caddy 2.11.4 (the current latest) ships a binary compiled with
# Go 1.26.3. Three Go stdlib CVEs were disclosed after that build
# landed upstream:
#   - CVE-2026-27145  crypto/x509 DoS
#   - CVE-2026-39822  os.Root symlink following
#   - CVE-2026-42504  mime DoS
# The fixed Go versions are 1.26.4 / 1.26.5; caddy:2.11.4-alpine
# predates the rebuild. We accept the risk because:
#   1. Aegis serves the panel UI (Vite SPA) via this Caddy instance —
#      no user-controlled path reaches crypto/x509 parsing here.
#   2. caddy:2-alpine is rebuilt by upstream monthly; next bump
#      (>= 2.11.5) will pick up the patched Go.
#   3. distroless Go-static backend image is unaffected (no Caddy).
# Action: re-evaluate on any of:
#   - Caddy 2.11.5 release notes mention Go >= 1.26.5
#   - A concrete exploit PoC for any of the three CVEs on a
#     static-file web server (current AVD attack vectors need
#     crafted client certs / arbitrary file roots, neither of
#     which the panel UI exposes).
CVE-2026-27145
CVE-2026-39822
CVE-2026-42504
